      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "GEMMY LOU (1) went back last start then made a long searching run to finish 12 metres from the winner in third at Wedderburn over 2150m, that effort following a good second at Charlton the run prior. Sure to enjoy an economical run from this draw. Meeting a deeper field this time but she good enough to play a major role. OHANA BY THE SEA (2) drew wide last start and was easily accounted for, beaten 13 metres into eighth at this track over 1609m. Tackles a similar assignment and from this more favourable draw she can feature in the finish. VOODOO RANGER NZ (3) disappointed last time when ninth over 1680m at Launceston. Can atone. LIFE ONA HIGHWAY (5) is in the mix following a respectable second at his most recent appearance over 2190m at Shepparton. Top-three conveyance.",
